<p><a name="intro2"></a>Well, as u can see, after some delay [MATRiX]#2 is out. There changed very important thing from the first planned release - editor. I know there could happened something more happier, anyway reality is hard and seems, nobody can chage it,...</p>
<p>I have never read editorial stuff of zines, so i have no fucking idea what to write here. Anyway, i think it is good place to thank our contributors especially thank to ZOMBiE who nearlly full filled our first zine. I hope due to new [MATRiX] members, [MATRiX]#2 isnt so full of foriners' stuff.</p>
<p>Despite of the first zine, [MATRiX]#2 is released in two versions - offline and online one. Long time before release we were discuss 'bout release type - HTML|DOS viewer|Win32 viewer,... etc. There was even idea release pure files with articles, viriis,... etc, (mine idea XXD))). Anyway Anaktos came with cool viewer so this stuf was done. As u can notice, [MATRiX]#2 is published in Win32 viewer. Online version can be reached on http://www.coderz.net/matrix/online.</p>
<p>And as allways, every stuff in this zine is for educationall purpose only. [MATRiX] group isn't resposibile for any damage caused by some stuff in this zine,...</p>
<p>Seems it's everything i can write here,...</p>
<div align="right">mort[MATRiX]</div>
